3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may be relevant to data structures and algorithms as it discusses the performance of LDPC codes decoded iteratively. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper may be relevant to social and information networks as LDPC codes are used in network coding and distributed storage systems. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may be relevant to computational complexity as it discusses the comparison of instanton-amoeba evaluations against standard Monte-Carlo calculations, which involves computational complexity analysis.
